Comment_glosser: Possibly, 20 is somehow derivable from 10 but I don't know enough about the historical phonology to judge this.
Synchronically, it looks like the order switched from 20+9 to 10+20 but this could also just be the way different tones interact in the language (?).
I suspect that the actual 20 is in fact in there but I cannot tell for sure.
I believe that t?ù(j)-lògy??j is a contracted form of 50. However, given the level of abstraction it may also be justified to view 50 as atomic in these compounded numerals?
The order of the last two elements could theoretically also be switched (see alternative glossing) but I consider this unlikely.
